</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,726,1257]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[608,754,726,753]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Horn Shark</emphasis>
. To at least 
<quantity box="[898,983,727,753]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.21" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="121.0">121 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1000,1083,727,754]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.20904" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="in" value="47.6">47.6 in</quantity>
) TL (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California). The widely reported maximum length of 
<quantity box="[308,392,799,825]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.22" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="122.0">122 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[408,469,799,826]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2192" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="in" value="48.0">48 in</quantity>
) TL (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[591,825,799,825]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
) is based on a statement in 
<bibRefCitation author="Roedel and Ripley" box="[1143,1436,798,825]" firstAuthor="Roedel" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref317822" refString="Roedel, P. M. &amp; Ripley, W. E. (1950) California sharks and rays. California Department of Fish and Game, Fish Bulletin, 75." type="book" year="1950">Roedel and Ripley (1950)</bibRefCitation>
that this species reached a maximum length of “about 
<quantity box="[799,861,835,861]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2192" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="ft" value="4.0">4 feet</quantity>
[= 
<quantity box="[891,982,834,861]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.22" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="122.0">122 cm</quantity>
].” Bolinas, northern California (Personal communication: Santa Barbara Natural History Museum Fish Collection, Santa Barbara, California) to Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[323,551,907,933]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
); reported to 
<collectingCountry box="[693,803,907,933]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(Mejîa-Falla 
<emphasis box="[953,1006,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2007), probably 
<collectingCountry box="[1192,1285,907,933]" name="Ecuador" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ebert" box="[1297,1424,907,933]" firstAuthor="Ebert" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref276228" refString="Ebert, D. A. (2003) Sharks, Rays, and Chimaeras of California. University of California Press, Berkeley." type="book" year="2003">Ebert 2003</bibRefCitation>
), and Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="Cornejo" box="[311,534,942,969]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cornejo" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1809" refId="ref271862" refString="Cornejo, R., Velez-Zuazo, X., Gonzalez-Pestana, A., Kouri J., C. &amp; Mucientes, G. (2015) An updated checklist of Chondrichthyes from the southeast Pacific off Peru. CheckList, 11, 1809. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 11.6.1809" type="journal article" year="2015">
Cornejo 
<emphasis box="[410,466,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Benthic; depth: intertidal to 
<quantity box="[867,938,943,969]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.01" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="201.0">201 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[952,1022,943,970]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.01168" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="ft" value="660.0">660 ft</quantity>
) (min.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Eschmeyer and Herald" box="[1111,1431,943,969]" firstAuthor="Eschmeyer" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref277744" refString="Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Herald, E. S. (1983) A Field Guide to Pacific Coast Fishes of North America from the Gulf of Alaska to Baja California. Houghton Mifflin, Boston." type="book" year="1983">Eschmeyer and Herald 1983</bibRefCitation>
; max.: Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California).
</paragraph>
